Date:9/27/2012 3:10:23 AM
From:Paul Senior
I believe the expense of listing or compliance is a concern for these Aussie
companies.

I'm aware of several small e&p companies that were set up in Australia and
followed a path of acquiring land in the USA, developing it or parts of it, and
then, as stock appreciated and/or to broaden the shareholder base, getting a
listing on a USA exchange. I've had no issues (capital structure/fraud) with
Canadian companies (with only the .to or .v listing) buying and developing only
or primarily land in the USA, so for me I don't see the problem with the
Australians doing the same thing.
